Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide chunks (no need
to peel!). Pop the potato on a low sided wide #baking tray{} in a single
layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to
coat, then spread out. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your
oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Drain and rinse the
@black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Pop half the black beans in a medium sized
#bowl{} and crush with the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot,
add the pepper slices and @Vivera Plant Chicken Pieces{175%g}. Cook stirring
occasionally until the pepper is tender and the Vivera pieces golden,
~{7-9%minutes}. Stir in the @Mexican spice{1} and @Mexican style spice mix{}
and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the black beans (whole and crushed), @BBQ sauce{64%g},
@vegetable stock powder{1} and @water{100%ml}. Stir everything together well.

Bring the pan to a boil and turn the heat down to simmer. Cook stirring
occasionally until the mixture has thickened slightly, ~{6-7%minutes}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper.

Once the potatoes and Vivera and pepper stew are cooked, tip the filling in to
an appropriately sized baking tray (we used a 20cm x 20cm tray for 2 people).
Evenly cover the filling with the cooked potatoes and sprinkle over the cheese.
Return to the top shelf of your oven and cook until the cheese is melted and the
filling bubbling, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Share the upside down loaded potatoes between your plates. Sprinkle over the
chopped spring onion. Enjoy!